deck: Architect of the Uber programme, which created the Panzermensch and Battleships.
description:
Origin

Using alien technology and scripts, General Sankt created Projekt U, an experimental programme which goal was to create enchanced humans. Most test subjects died, but 1 in 5000 survived the experiments and became either Panzermensch (with limited powers) or Battleships (with almost unlimited powers).

After British spy Stephanie had sabotaged the programme and had returned to London with her research notes, General Sankt reported back to Hitler. Because of his failure, Hitler had Battleship Siegfried kill Sankt.
name: General Sankt

description: She was a high school swimming star until her mutation was revealed.

deck: Lupin Schultz was a Panzermensch, an enhanced human with a portion of the powers of the Battleships.
description:
Origin

WWII scientists had created a serum which could endow humans with enhanced speed, strength and invulnerability. Some humans would reach the full potential of these powers (they were called Battleships) and other would get just a portion of these powers (they were called Panzermensch). Lupin Schultz was a Panzermensch. He was used by the British spy Stephanie, who was known as Freya Bergen to the Nazis, as her bodyguard when she secretly went back to England with the serum. During a stop, Lupin relieved himself in the bushes and was shot in the back by Stephanie, who knew his powers were at their weakest. He was the first Panzermensch killed in action.
name: Lupin Schultz

deck: Rudoph Gelt was a Panzermensch, an enhanced human with a portion of the powers of the Battleships.
description:
Origin

WWII scientists had created a serum which could endow humans with enhanced speed, strength and invulnerability. Some humans would reach the full potential of these powers (they were called Battleships) and other would get just a portion of these powers (they were called Panzermensch). Rudoph Gelt was a Panzermensch. He was killed by the British spy Stephanie, who was known as Freya Bergen to the Nazis, when she shot through his disruption halo, which then became unstable and ripped his head apart. He was the second Panzermensch killed in action.
name: Rudoph Gelt

deck: Anita Scheele was General Sankt's adjudant.
description:
Origin

Anita Scheele was a sculptress in Berlin before World War II broke out. Somehow she became General Sankt's adjudant, until he died. She then schemed with other generals and Battleship Siegmund to kill Adolf Hitler. Siegmund seemingly succeeded in killing Hitler, but he later turned up alive. She has displayed powers of energy manipulation, like the Panzermensch.
name: Anita Scheele

deck: Matthias Scholtz was a Panzermensch, an enhanced human with a portion of the powers of the Battleships.
description:
Origin

WWII scientists had created a serum which could endow humans with enhanced speed, strength and invulnerability. Some humans would reach the full potential of these powers (they were called Battleships) and other would get just a portion of these powers (they were called Panzermensch). Matthias Scholtz was a Panzermensch. He was deployed in Paris, France with Battleship Sieglinde. They encountered a resistance force of Allied enchanced humans. He was the first Panzermensch killed by another enhanced human.
name: Matthias Scholtz

deck: The first Allied enhanced human, created with the stolen technology from the Germans.
description:
Origin

Patrick O'Connor was an American air fighter. While stationed in London, he became a test subject for the stolen German technology, with which the Germans had created their Battleships and Panzermensch. He survived the experiments and became their first HMH (Her Majesty's Human).

Taking the codename Colossus, his first fight was again Battleship Sieglinde. She had invaded Paris with a troupe of Panzermensch. Together with other enhanced humans, Colossus fought one-on-one against Sieglinde. Trying to choke her, she tore off both his arms and mutilated his body with her powers. Invulnerable, Colossus didn't die from the mutilation. The Allied Forces euthanized Colossus by using an industrial drill.
name: Colossus

deck: Younger brother of the HMH Colossus, Patrick O'Connor.
description:
Origin

Originally from Hell's Kitchen, New York City, the young Eamonn O'Connor was stationed in Okinawa, Japan during World War II. Almost killed by the Miyoko Yoshiuki, he was found by the American Forces and taken back to America. His fraternal connection to the first HMH, the Colossus, made the Americans think that Eamonn himself had also the potential to become an enhanced human. They named him USS Colossus (with a nod to his older brother).
name: USS Colossus

deck: Crossbones (Nicholas) is from a parallel reality, he used his powers to destroy his reality's heroes in retaliation of the utter destruction of his home-planet.
description:
Origin

Crossbones was born as Nicholas, a bright young boy. He grew up in a parallel reality on a distant paradise-like planet. His father was a space-cop whom fought an intergalactic war. Nicholas looked up to his father a great deal and his father's friends; that reality's Captain America and Nick Fury. Although the war raged on in the galaxy, Nicholas had peaceful childhood and was best friends with Mr. Lobkins, and android home-keeper. It was however then that the war came to Nicholas' home-planet. In a surprise attack, the whole small world was devastated, with most of it's residents dead and Nicholas gravely wounded to one of his eyes. The enormous failure of the space-heroes to stop this attack caused Nicholas to alter his views as he became embittered and looking for revenge as he grew older.

Creation

Crossbones (Nicholas) was created by Ales Kot and Marco Rudy and first appeared in Bucky Barnes: The Winter Soldier issue 3 (2015). He is not to be mistaken for the 616 universe villain Crossbones (Brock Rumlow)..

Major Story Arcs

Vengeance on the Heroes

Nicholas wanted revenge for the events that destroyed his home-planet and the lack of protection the heroes where supposed to give to his small paradise planet. Nicholas donned the identity Crossbones and embarked on a mission of revenge. Traveling towards Earth, Nicholas fought against it's heroes in great success and seemingly killed all but was not able to kill Bucky Barnes. The killings had a profound impact on Nicholas, causing him nightmares. The fact that Bucky had survived caused a bitter rivalry between the two, which never really saw a winner. Eventually, during one of their battles, that reality''s Bucky seemingly managed to kill Nicholas. Things where however far from over. Nicholas survives and planed another round of revenge.

To 616 Reality

Nicholas had survived his encounter with his reality's older Bucky Barnes and had traveled to the 616 (or main Marvel) universe in order to kill both Bucky Barnes and Ventolin Xtal, the woman whom 616 Bucky had a relationship with.It turned out that Nicholas was hired by King Loki to take the planet of Mer-Z-Bow hostage. If the planet would not give up it's primary recources, which could be made into drugs, Nicholas had the job of destroying the whole planet. Luckily howver, Daisy Johnson, Bucky from the 616 reality and his future counterpart worked together in stopping Crossbones. He was eventually killed when he tried to escape back to his own reality.
name: Crossbones (Barnes)

deck: The man called Dr. Mime was a masked hero in the late 1980's, he was a member of the First Line.
description:
Creation

Doctor Mime was a character created for the comic book series published by Marvel Comics called the First Line and was created by Roger Stern and John Byrne.

History

The man calling himself Dr. Mime was a masked hero during the late 1980's. He remains a mystery as his background was never relieved. he was a member of the First Line. He was present when their leader Effigy questioned a Skrull spy who was captured by scientist Reed Richards over the impending Skrull invasion of Earth. Doctor Mime has not been seen since, and it is unknown if he was among the team's final conflict against the Skrull Empire a few years later.
name: Doctor Mime

deck: Positron is an African-American woman with an gadgets which expel powerful bolts of energy. She first appeared as a villain who fought against the First Line. She was the lover of Blackjack.
description:
Creation

Positron was created by John Byrne and Roger Stern and debuted in the Marvel:The Lost Generation, published by Marvel Comics.

History

Positron was an African American woman who took the identity of a costumed villain during the 1960's. She had somehow either come across or created certain gadgets which allowed her to shoot force blasts from her gauntlets. She not only had worked as a hired mercenary and crook for several agencies at the time but appears to had been a partner to the one time crook Blackjack. The two had also m

When the invasion finally came, the First Line gathered all their surviving members past and present as well as their various foes to work together to stop the invasion, boarding the Skrull mother-ship in an attempt to stop it. Among those involved in the battle included Positron herself.

The battle was witnessed by Cassandra Locke who was arriving on her first jump into the past and witnessed the battle. When Blackjack was killed and Positron arrived too late to rescue him, Cassandra stated that his death was her fault. Shocked and angered at her lovers death Positron took it out on the remaining Skrull forces. Soon the team's leader Effigy was mortally wounded trying to set warp-feed phase-shifters to destruct. Dying he reverted back into his Skrull form before Pixie and Oxbow telling them he tried to be a good American before he died. Pixie then set the destruct sequence, the resulting explosion destroyed the entire alien fleet and seemingly slew all those who had not already died in battle, including its assumed Positron.

Power and Abilities

Positron is a normal human being with average strength, agility, and stamina.

Positron did possess a pair of Power Gauntlets which were attached to portable power packs which were capable of blasting powerful bolts of energy.
name: Positron

deck: Blake Burdick is a police officer and the new husband of Peggy Rae, ex-wife of Scott Lang (Ant-Man) and Cassie Lang (Stature)
description:
Origin

Blake Burdick was an NYPD officer who came into contact with Peggy Rae, the ex-wife of Scott Lang.

Creation

Blake Burdick was created by Geoff Johns and Gary Frank and first appeared in Avengers Vol.3 issue 62 (2003).

Major Story Arcs

A New Relationship

Blake and Rae soon started dating and eventually the two moved in and married, with Blake trying to become somewhat of a stepfather to Cassie. She, however, did not want much to do with Blake as he and Peggy started to grow a resentment to Cassie's father and his way of handling her.

A New Life

After the apparent death of Peggy's ex-husband, Blake and Peggy could not stop Cassie from following in her father's footsteps to become a superhero. This eventually led to Cassie's death at the hands of Doctor Doom, right at the moment that Scott returned from the dead. Some months later, Cassie was revived by a guilt-ridden Doctor Doom. The second chance Peggy and Blake had with her daughter caused them to move to Miami, away from the superhero grace in New York City.

Other Media

Film

Ant-Man (2015)

Blake Burdick appears in the Ant-Man film. However, the character has been renamed Paxton and will be portrayed by actor Bobby Cannavale.
